50|$|On October 12, 2007, the Holy Synod of the Patriarchate of Moscow, {{under the}} {{chairmanship}} of Patriarch Alexis resolved to <b>grant</b> canonical <b>letters</b> <b>of</b> release to those clergymen (priests and deacons, nothing being said concerning readers and minor clergy) who had sought to leave the Diocese of Sourozh to join Bishop Basil's vicariate. This decision was made {{in response to a}} request on September 23 by Archbishop Gabriel <b>of</b> Comana to <b>grant</b> <b>letters</b> <b>of</b> release to the priests and deacons who had followed Bishop Basil into the Exarchate of Russian Orthodox Parishes in Western Europe.|$|R
